Subject: [PATCH 6/9] AI-2091: wire G2 fetchability + G4 pre-mutation CAS onto
 the live dispatch path
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Code-review (CodeReviewAgent, 21:34:51Z) bounced the branch: two gates shipped
as dead code (the AI-1808 failure mode this umbrella exists to close). Fix both
on their real production paths with boot-path integration tests that fail red
against the unwired HEAD.

G2 phantomFetchabilityGate — was invoked only in processStaleSession (C4 re-poke).
The primary webhook path (the actual phantom source: AI-2014 16:45Z, the AI-2034
dead-identifier cluster) had no existence gate. checkLinearIssueRouting now
surfaces terminalNotFound (OK response + null issue), and dispatchRoute runs
assertDispatchTargetFetchable before delivery: a confirmed phantom aborts with a
first-class phantom-dispatch-abort event and ZERO delivery; a transient fetch
failure still fails open. Gate marked active at the createWebhookRouter wiring
site, not a bootstrap literal.

G4 preMutationCAS — assertMutationAgainstCurrentState had no call site. It is now
invoked in handleProxyRequest before the upstream forward. The ticket delegate is
captured at command start on CommandAuthSnapshot (snapshotTicketDelegate), and a
TRAILING governed issueUpdate is rejected (stale-snapshot-mutation-rejected) only
when a FOREIGN actor took the delegate mid-run — the delegate drifted from the
snapshot AND is no longer the caller. Self-progression is never false-rejected:
the state dimension is neutralized (commandAuthSnapshots reuses command-start
state by design, AI-1848/1872/1924) and a trailing self-progression step is a
commentCreate, not gated; a first mutation is already gated live by
checkWorkflowRules. Transient re-reads fail open.

Tests (both red on 331ac50, green now):
- ai-2091-g2-fetchability-wiring.test.ts: boots createApp, drives a signed webhook
  for an unfetchable ticket through the production path, asserts phantom-dispatch-
  abort + zero delivery.
- ai-2091-g4-cas-wiring.test.ts: drives a foreign-actor stale mutation through
  handleProxyRequest (rejected) and a multi-step self-progression (passes),
  plus an unchanged-delegate trailing mutation (passes).

Full suite 175 suites / 4282 tests green; tsc --noEmit clean.

