MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two features, one commit:

Feature 1: Per-ticket dispatch circuit breaker
- After 3 consecutive wakes where the workflow state hasn't changed, trip
  the breaker and stop re-dispatching
- Emits one loud alert (transition-stuck: <ticket> <state> — N wakes,
  no progress) via the alert bus
- Parks dispatch until the state label advances or a steward calls
  resetBreaker()
- Breaker is per-ticket, not per-agent — other tickets to the same
  delegate continue normally
- State tracking in an in-memory Map<ticketId, TicketBreakerState>
- Resets automatically on state advance (recordDispatch detects state
  label change and resets counter)
- Exposed at /health.dispatchCircuitBreaker

Feature 2: Comment-fed re-wake suppression (pre-wake heuristic)
- Before the breaker counter increments, check if the event is a comment
  authored by the ticket's current delegate with an unchanged state:*
  label — if so, suppress the wake without incrementing the counter
- Kills the dominant observed loop (steward comment → native state
  side-effect → dispatcher sees activity → re-wakes → same failing
  transition) at the source

Wiring:
- Hooked into dispatchRoute in webhook/index.ts, right after the
  AI-1918 idempotency check and before the stale-route guard
- State label extracted from event payload labels (supports both
  direct Issue labels and nested Comment→issue labels)
- Follows the AI-1808 dead-code-in-prod guard pattern:
  /health.dispatchCircuitBreaker is exposed from the real module

Test coverage:
- 20 tests: breaker enrollment, counter increment, trip at threshold,
  state-advance reset, explicit reset, comment-fed suppression,
  case-insensitive author matching, health endpoint shape

Closes AI-2178.
